This paper deals with decision procedures for satisfiability of modal and description logics, which are typically studied in the area of computational logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses automata-based approaches, which are commonly used in the area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for solving problems related to formal languages and automata theory. The paper also mentions the use of on-the-fly techniques, which are often studied in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for optimizing algorithms. The paper also discusses the implementation and optimization of a specific algorithm, which falls under the area of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the theoretical aspects of modal logic, which is a subfield of mathematical logic (cs.PL).
